HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 956
By Darby
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Dr. Brooke Spivey
Burress upon being named Young Optometrist
of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Dr. Brooke Spivey Burress, who was named
Young Optometrist of the Year at the Tennessee Association of Optometric Physicians Annual
Congress in October 2025; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of McKenzie High School, Dr. Spivey Burress continued her
education at the University of Tennessee at Martin and the Southern College of Optometry, from
which she graduated with honors in May 2021; and
WHEREAS, she began her professional practice at Spivey Eye Clinic in McKenzie,
continuing the practice established by her father and grandfather and upholding a longstanding
family commitment to serving the vision care needs of her community; and
WHEREAS, in her fourth year of practice, Dr. Spivey Burress has already distinguished
herself within her profession, earning recognition as Young Optometrist of the Year and
representing the promise and excellence of optometry's next generation; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Brooke Spivey Burress epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are
characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Spivey Burress is most grateful for the love and companionship she
shares with her husband, Corey Burress, who also contributes to the family practice as an
optician at Spivey Eye Clinic; and
HJR0956
013294
- 1 -

WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to pause in our deliberations to acknowledge and
applaud Dr. Brooke Spivey Burress for her dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Dr. Brooke Spivey Burress upon being named
Young Optometrist of the Year and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
